Five useful git commands:


Commands




git add --all
 - Adds all changes that you have made.


git commit -m
 - Commit your changes to Git history and submit a commit message.


git push -u master
 - Push changes to remote repository branch.


git status
 - Allows you to check status of the changes you have made.


git log
 - Check the history of all commits to the branch you are currently on.




Steps to be productive in Git.




Commit often


Push working code


Don't panic
